Definition.WordDefinition: Sea gull \Sea" gull`\ (Zo["o]l.) Any gull living on the seacoast. [1913 Webster]
sea gull n : mostly white aquatic bird having long pointed wings and short legs [syn: {gull}, {seagull}]
seagull n : mostly white aquatic bird having long pointed wings and short legs [syn: {gull}, {sea gull}]
